---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ReadMenu from "../components/ReadMenu.astro";
import "../styles/pages/home.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Liberation and Inclusion Translation"
  description="A trauma-informed, justice-oriented translation of the Bible from the original languages."
  canonical="https://litbible.net/"
  bg="green"
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-wrap container">
      <svg
        class="hero-shape"
        viewBox="0 0 1000 520"
        preserveAspectRatio="none"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <path
          fill="var(--cream)"
          d="
            M 80 0
            L 920 0

            C 960 60, 960 160, 920 260
            C 880 360, 880 460, 920 520

            L 80 520

            C 40 460, 40 360, 80 260
            C 120 160, 120 60, 80 0
            Z
          "
        ></path>
      </svg>

      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-inner">
          <p class="hero-lead">
            The Bible is a library of sacred literature from oppressed &amp;
            marginalized communities.
          </p>

          <p class="hero-question">
            <em>
              So why do we translate it to justify more trauma,
              authoritarianism, and exclusion?
            </em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TITLE + READ MENU -->
  <section
    class="title-block title-block--with-menu"
    aria-labelledby="lit-title"
  >
    <div class="title-block__inner container">
      <p class="title-small">Introducing</p>

      <h1 id="lit-title" class="title-stack">
        <span class="title-medium">The</span>
        <span class="title-large">Liberation</span>
        <span class="title-medium">and</span>
        <span class="title-large">Inclusion</span>
        <span class="title-large">Translation</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="title-small title-sub">of the Christian Scriptures</p>
    </div>

    <div class="title-menu container">
      <ReadMenu />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section class="intro" aria-labelledby="intro-title">
    <div class="intro-inner container">
      <h2 id="intro-title" class="intro-eyebrow">Hi there. I’m Brandon.</h2>

      <p class="intro-lead">
        No, I don’t want my kids near most Bibles, either.
      </p>

      <p class="intro-lead">I don’t want it to hurt them like it hurt me.</p>

      <p class="intro-lead">
        That’s why I’ve been translating it for them since 2020.
      </p>

      <p class="intro-body">
        All from a trauma-informed, cringe-mindful, liberationist lens.
      </p>

      <p class="intro-body">One Greek word at a time.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CALLOUT -->
  <section class="callout" data-animate="underline">
    <div class="callout-inner container">
      <div class="callout-panel">
        <h2 class="callout-head">
          Turns out there’s some
          <span class="callout-underline">
            really
            <svg
              class="callout-underline-svg"
              viewBox="0 0 220 26"
              aria-hidden="true"
              focusable="false"
            >
              <path
                class="callout-underline-path"
                d="M6 18 C 55 6, 120 6, 214 16"></path>
            </svg>
          </span>
          good stuff in there.
        </h2>

        <a
          class="callout-cta footer-cta"
          href="/read"
          aria-label="Read the Liberation and Inclusion Translation now"
        >
          <span>Read Now</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout-diagonal" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Underline animation -->
  <script type="module">
    (() => {
      const sections = document.querySelectorAll('[data-animate="underline"]');
      if (sections.length === 0) return;

      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries, obs) => {
          for (const entry of entries) {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              entry.target.classList.add("is-visible");
              obs.unobserve(entry.target);
            }
          }
        },
        { threshold: 0.35 }
      );

      sections.forEach((s) => observer.observe(s));
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- CHAT -->
  <section class="chat-block" aria-labelledby="chat-block-title">
    <div class="chat-block__inner container">
      <h2 id="chat-block-title" class="sr-only">
        A conversation about salvation and liberation
      </h2>

      <div class="chat-thread">
        <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--left" data-animate="in">
          <p>Tell me more of this <em>good stuff</em>…</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--right" data-animate="in">
          <p>
            “Salvation” was one of the first words I worked through. I picture
            floating on clouds, being rescued from hell. The sinner’s prayer,
            and all that.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--left" data-animate="in">
          <p>That’s not what salvation is about?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--right" data-animate="in">
          <p>
            Well, to a lot of Christians it is. But that word traps them in the
            wrong story. Jesus freed the oppressed and cast down the mighty.
            That sounds less like salvation and more like…
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--left chat-bubble--center"
          data-animate="in"
        >
          <p>Liberation</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-bubble chat-bubble--right" data-animate="in">
          <p>Exactly! Did you scroll ahead or something?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Chat animation -->
  <script type="module">
    (() => {
      const reduceMotion = window.matchMedia(
        "(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)"
      ).matches;
      if (reduceMotion) return;

      const els = document.querySelectorAll('[data-animate="in"]');
      if (!("IntersectionObserver" in window) || els.length === 0) return;

      const io = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          for (const entry of entries) {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              entry.target.classList.add("is-in");
              io.unobserve(entry.target);
            }
          }
        },
        { threshold: 0.15 }
      );

      els.forEach((el, i) => {
        if (!(el instanceof HTMLElement)) return;
        el.style.setProperty("--stagger", `${i * 70}ms`);
        io.observe(el);
      });
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- QUESTIONS -->
  <section class="questions-block" aria-labelledby="questions-title">
    <div class="questions-block__inner container">
      <h2 id="questions-title" class="questions-block__title">
        I’ve got more questions…
      </h2>

      <div class="questions-grid">
        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <article class="question-card">
          <div class="question-card__media">
            <img
              src="/images/open-bible.webp"
              alt="A hand holding a glass sphere reflecting a city at sunset"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>

          <h3 class="question-card__question">
            What values guide this effort?
          </h3>

          <p class="question-card__answer">
            Faithfulness to the Greek, reading with the damned, sidestepping
            religious jargon, trusting that God is always like Jesus, and more.
          </p>

          <a
            class="question-cta"
            href="/translation-commitments"
            aria-label="Read the translation commitments"
          >
            <span>More about Commitments</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <article class="question-card">
          <div class="question-card__media">
            <img
              src="/images/upside-down.webp"
              alt="An open Bible with reference books and handwritten notes"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>

          <h3 class="question-card__question">
            Who are you, to translate the Bible?!
          </h3>

          <p class="question-card__answer">
            Let’s start with the first three words of that question…
          </p>

          <a
            class="question-cta"
            href="/about"
            aria-label="Learn about Brandon and the project background"
          >
            <span>I’m just a person</span>
          </a>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <article class="question-card">
          <div class="question-card__media">
            <img
              src="/images/fit-cover.webp"
              alt="Found in Translation podcast artwork under a magnifying glass"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>

          <h3 class="question-card__question">
            What if I’m more of an auditory learner?
          </h3>

          <p class="question-card__answer">
            I cohost a podcast where we work through the LIT one chapter or big
            idea at a time. It’s called “Found in Translation.”
          </p>

          <a
            class="question-cta"
            href="/podcast"
            aria-label="Listen to the Found in Translation podcast"
          >
            <span>Listen now</span>
          </a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
